==Description==

The '''Std DockOverlayToggleRight''' command provides a shortcut to quickly show or hide the entire group of panels that are currently in the [[Std_DockOverlayAll|overlay system]] on the right side of the screen.

This command does not move panels into or out of the overlay system; it only toggles the visibility of the right overlay container itself. This is a convenience feature for users who want to temporarily hide all panels on one side of the view to maximize their workspace without having to exit the overlay mode completely.

==Usage==

# The [[Std_DockOverlayAll|overlay mode]] must be active, and there must be at least one panel in the right overlay area.
# There are several ways to invoke the command:
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|View → Dock panel overlay → Toggle right}} option from the menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|Ctrl}}+{{KEY|Right}}.
#* Use the overlay toggle right button ([[File:Std DockOverlayToggleRight.svg|12x12px]]) from a docked window's title bar.

